Quote:  We'd make dumplings, too, fried up in the camp oven. Buggers afloat we called them [c1916] ... And what did we call the poached eggs? A pair of bastards on a raft, and we'd have tits on toast - belly pickled pork on toast. I still use those old names; everyone laughs at me.
Notes:  (Bill Henderson)


